THE LIPTON CHAMPIONSHIPS
March 21, 1998
Marcelo Rios
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 
Q.  Was this a hard match for you, Marcelo? 
 
MARCELO RIOS: I think it was really tough first round.  I feel really good.  I think I played really good. 
 

Q.  Was it good to have a tough opponent first round?
 
MARCELO RIOS: Sure. I played him first round last week also.  We had a tough match.  It was tough to play today, really windy.  And the conditions are not very good. But I think I served really good and I was playing really good at baseline. 
 

Q.  Does winning a tournament make you much more confident?
 
MARCELO RIOS: Sure.  Coming from Indian Wells, you come with -- I am playing really good first round.  I think that is really good. 
 

Q.  Who is your toughest opponent on the Tour?
 
MARCELO RIOS: I think everybody is tough. 
 

Q.  Have you read the Sports Illustrated article?
 
MARCELO RIOS: Yeah. 
 

Q.  Your thoughts on that.
 
MARCELO RIOS: Well, I think this guy that wrote the  article, before the interview, he knew what he was going to write.  So that is fine.  I don't care what he wrote.  Like I say before, he make all the questions, you know, really what he -- he knew what he was going to do. 
 

Q.  What do you like to do off the tennis court?
 
MARCELO RIOS: I like to play golf, play soccer sometimes. 
 

End of FastScripts....

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT